dcterms:description: The graph is based on the road network of Minnesota, where each node represents the intersections of roads and the edges represent the roads connecting these intersections. The graph considered has 376 nodes and 455 edges, constrained to specific coordinates.
dcterms:title: Minnesota Road Network

dcterms:creator: A. Bay
B. Sengupta
dcterms:description: Paths between two randomly selected nodes are calculated using the A∗ algorithm, which is a best-first search algorithm that evaluates paths yielding the smallest cost based on distance and heuristic estimates.
dcterms:title: A∗ Algorithm Paths

dcterms:description: The dataset is used for training sequence-to-sequence models, which are widely applied in tasks such as text translation and other sequence prediction tasks.
dcterms:title: Sequence-to-Sequence Learning
